<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-export SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/evernote-export4.dtd">
<en-export export-date="20260611T073846Z" application="Evernote" version="11.9.1">
  <note>
    <title>00. No CMV, HP, fungus, invasive CA</title>
    <created>20160916T084305Z</created>
    <updated>20241112T072534Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>    </div><div>No Helicobacter Pylori is demonstrated by <span style="color:#fc1233;">Giemsa</span> stain.</div><div>    </div><div>There is focal <span style="color:#fc1233;">crush artifact </span>makes the cytologic interpretation difficult. </div><div><br/></div><div>No viral inclusion is demonstrated by anti-<span style="color:#fc1233;">CMV</span> immunostain.        </div><div>No fungus is highlighted by <span style="color:#fc1233;">PAS</span>.        </div><div>No Helicobacter Pylori is demonstrated by <span style="color:#fc1233;">Giemsa</span> stain.    </div><div>No invasive carcinoma is demonstrated by <span style="color:#fc1233;">AE1/AE3.  </span>   </div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Microsoft YaHei';">Immunohistochemical stain for H. pylori reveals no organisms.     </span></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Microsoft YaHei';">Immunohistochemical stain for H. pylori reveals rare  organisms within the mucous layer. </span></div><div>    </div><div>    </div><div style="text-align:start;color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">No fungus is highlighted by GMS and PAS. </div><div><br/></div><div>No fungus is highlighted by PAS.</div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">No mycobacterial microorganisms are identified by</span> <span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="color:#fc1233;">acid fast </span>stain.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Microsoft YaHei';">The proliferation index as determined by <span style="color:#fc1233;">Ki67</span> shows no significant increase.</span></div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, <span style="color:rgb(252, 18, 51);">CD3 and CD20 </span>demonstrate normal distribution of T and B lymphocytes. </div><div>Neither invasive carcinoma nor lymphoepithelial lesion is demonstrated by AE1/AE3.    </div><div><br/></div><div>The accompanying lymphoid infiltrate comprises a mixture of <span style="color:#fc1233;">CD3</span>-positive T cells and <span style="color:#fc1233;">CD20</span>-positive B cells. The lymphoid cells of germinal center are negative for bcl-2</div><div>No invasive carcinoma is demonstrated by <span style="color:#fc1233;">AE1/AE3.  </span>   </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>abnormal MMR</title>
    <created>20200115T043704Z</created>
    <updated>20251216T093425Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Adenocarcinoma, with abnormal result of IHC for mismatch repair testing (see description).</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Acute appendicitis with serrated adenoma</title>
    <created>20180910T015154Z</created>
    <updated>20231012T073943Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Acute appendicitis with serrated adenoma</div><div><br/></div><div>Sections show appendiceal tissue featuring serrated adenoma. The adenoma shows</div><div>architectural complexity with serrations extending into the crypt bases, which are</div><div>dilated. The lining epithelial cells show focally mild dysplasia. The appendiceal wall</div><div>is diffusely infiltrated by PMNs.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20170509T052659Z</created>
    <updated>20170509T052715Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Acute appendicitis with serrated adenoma</div><div><br/></div><div>Sections show appendiceal tissue featuring serrated adenoma. The adenoma shows</div><div>architectural complexity with serrations extending into the crypt bases, which are</div><div>dilated. The lining epithelial cells show focally mild dysplasia. The appendiceal wall</div><div>is diffusely infiltrated by PMNs.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Acute appendicitis, gangrenous and perforated.</title>
    <created>20180326T100851Z</created>
    <updated>20231012T074002Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Appendix, appendectomy --- Acute appendicitis, gangrenous and perforated.</div><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><div>The specimen consists of an appendix measuring _ cm in length and ___ cm in diameter.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and submitted in one cassette.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The appendicial wall is diffusely infiltrated by dense PMNs with gangrenous change and loss of its architecture. Focal abscess formation is noted. The serosa is coated by fibrinopurulent exudate. No malignancy is observed.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Acute colitis</title>
    <created>20161223T050905Z</created>
    <updated>20230616T071949Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>acute colitis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows colonic mucosal fragments revealing intact glands and neutrophilic infiltrate in the lamina propria. No evidence of malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Acute colitis (clinical r/o IBD)</title>
    <created>20170202T081857Z</created>
    <updated>20230616T071944Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Acute colitis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows colonic mucosal tissue with ulceration and mixed inflammatory</div><div>infiltrate in the lamina propria. Crypt abscess and focal crypt distortion are seen.</div><div>No viral inclusion is highlighted by anti-CMV immunostain. Inflammatory bowel disease</div><div>should be excluded clinically. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>AdenoCA_stomach [stoadeno]</title>
    <created>20160726T071219Z</created>
    <updated>20230804T074006Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Adenocarcinoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows gastric tissue with neoplastic cells featuring enlarged nuclei and prominent nucleoli arranged in villoglandular and cribriform patterns. </div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12px;">No Helicobacter Pylori is seen. </span></span></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are highlighted by cytokeratin (AE1/AE3).</div><div><br/></div><div>Her-2 (by immunohistochemistry): </div><div>+___ Negative (score 0) + ___ Negative (score 1+) + ___ Equivocal (score 2+) + ___ Positive (score 3+) + ___ Cannot be determined</div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been reviewed by two pathologists.)</div><div><br/></div><en-media style="--en-naturalWidth:692; --en-naturalHeight:396;" hash="d2765bbe5be4e4150ad35c0f078d7621" type="image/png" /><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
