  <note>
    <title>Adenocarcinoma, colon [COLadeno]</title>
    <created>20160914T070038Z</created>
    <updated>20260407T065438Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source-url>file:///C:\Users\h3d0\Desktop\Form_Huang\9-colorectal%20cancer.doc</source-url>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Adenocarcinoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows complex tubuloglandular structures lined by neoplastic columnar cells in a desmoplastic stroma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemical stains:</div><div>BRAF(V600E): Negative </div><div><br/></div><div>IHC Testing for Mismatch Repair (MMR) Proteins</div><div>  MLH1: Intact nuclear expression</div><div>  MSH2: Intact nuclear expression</div><div>  MSH6: Intact nuclear expression</div><div>  PMS2: Intact nuclear expression</div><div>IHC Interpretation: No loss of nuclear expression of MMR proteins: low probability of microsatellite instability-high (MSI-H).</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been reviewed by two pathologists.)</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Adenoma, intestinal-type, high-grade dysplasia [stomach_TA]</title>
    <created>20250305T025712Z</created>
    <updated>20250305T033201Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Intestinal-type adenoma with high grade dysplasia.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows gastric mucosal tissue with crowded tubuloglandular structures that are lined by columnar epithelium in which individual cells exhibit high grade dysplasia.</div><div><br/></div><div><b><a href="https://www.pathologyoutlines.com/topic/esophagusadenocarcinomaintramucosal.html" rev="en_rl_none"><span style="color:rgb(5, 79, 150);">Intramucosal adenocarcinoma</span></a><span style="color:rgb(5, 79, 150);"> Criteria</span></b></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Adenoma, intestinal-type, low-grade dysplasia [stomach_TA]</title>
    <created>20180822T035526Z</created>
    <updated>20231031T043843Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>adenoma, intestinal-type, low-grade dysplasia.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows gastric mucosal tissue with crowded</div><div>tubuloglandular structures that are lined by tall columnar</div><div>epithelium in which individual cells exhibit low-grade</div><div>dysplasia. Intestinal metaplasia and chronic inflammatory</div><div>infiltrate in the lamina propria are seen in the background.</div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;">No Helicobacter Pylori is seen. </span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Adenomatous lesion</title>
    <created>20160914T023604Z</created>
    <updated>20210311T014138Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Adenomatous lesion.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows an adenomatous lesion with villous architecture. The lining glandular epithelial cells have hyperchromatic nuclei with pseudostratifications. The lamina propria is edematous and inflamed. No invasion is identified.  Although no definite evidence of malignancy is noted, re-biopsy or close follow-up is suggested.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>anal fissure</title>
    <created>20211109T020547Z</created>
    <updated>20211109T020719Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><span style="font-family: gotham;">Anus, fissurectomy--- fissure.</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px; margin-top: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em;"><div><span style="font-family: gotham;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham;">Section shows ulcerated transitional or columnar mucosa with acute and chronic inflammation, granulation tissue, reactive and regenerative epithelial changes or foreign body giant cell reaction.</span></div></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Anal tag, anus</title>
    <created>20160726T072915Z</created>
    <updated>20230629T033011Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Anal tag</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows loose fibrovascular tissue covered by squamous epithelium. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div><span>    </span><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Angiodysplasia with hemorrhage and infarct.</title>
    <created>20180313T010505Z</created>
    <updated>20230608T053908Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">PATHOLOGICAL DIAGNOSIS:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Angiodysplasia with hemorrhage and infarct.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Sections reveal increased number of tortuous small to </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">medium-sized vessels in the submucosa and subserosa. The</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">vessels are dilated and lined by mildly pump endothelial </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">cells and have a thin layer of smooth muscle. Hemorrhagic</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">necrosis from mucosal to inner muscular propria with </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">neutrophilic infiltration is present. </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Bilateral resection ends are viable. There is no evidence</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">for malignancy.</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>APP_Acute appendicitis [APP1]</title>
    <created>20170620T082335Z</created>
    <updated>20260422T065733Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Acute appendicitis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:    </div><div>PMN infiltration of the mucosa, submucosa and muscular layers is noted. The serosa is congested.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>APP_acute suppurative appendicitis [APP4]</title>
    <created>20170620T082357Z</created>
    <updated>20260318T073617Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Appendix, appendectomy --- Acute suppurative appendicitis.</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The appendix measures __ cm in length, __ cm in diameter. The serosal</div><div>surface is markedly congested, rough and coated with fibrinopurulent material.</div><div>The lumen contains pus.</div><div>    </div><div>Representative sections are submitted in one cassette.</div><div><br/></div><div style="padding-left:40px;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div style="padding-left:40px;">The appendicial wall is diffusely infiltrated by dense PMNs. Focal abscess formation is noted. The serosa is coated by fibrinopurulent exudate.    </div><div>        </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>APP_early acute appendicitis</title>
    <created>20170628T061019Z</created>
    <updated>20231031T063957Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Appendix, appendectomy --- Early acute appendicitis.</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The appendix measures __ cm in length and __ cm in diameter. The serosal surface is mildly congested.  The lumen contains fecal material. </div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are submitted in one cassette.</div><div><br/></div><div>Early acute appendicitis</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Acute inflammatory cells are found within the mucosa with few PMNs being</div><div>present in the muscle layer. The serosal layer is free of inflammation.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
