<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Appendix, appendectomy --- Fecalith.</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The appendix measures __ cm in length, __ cm in diameter. The serosal surface is minimally congested.</div><div>The lumen contains fecal material.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are submitted in one cassette.</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The appendix is impacted with fecal material. The wall is free of PMN infiltration.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>APP_fibrous obliterans</title>
