<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="padding-left:40px;">-- chronic gastritis with Helicobacter pylori</div><div style="padding-left:40px;">   infection.</div><div style="padding-left:40px;">-- intestinal metaplasia.</div><div style="padding-left:40px;"><br/></div><div style="padding-left:40px;"><br/></div><div style="padding-left:40px;">Microscopic description:</div><div style="padding-left:40px;">Section shows gastric mucosal tissue with chronic inflammatory infiltrate expanding the lamina propria. Intestinal metaplasia is also seen. Some Helicobacter Pylori microorganism are highlighted by Giemsa stain.</div><div style="padding-left:40px;">Neither lymphoepithelial lesion nor invasive carcinoma is demonstrated by AE1/AE3.</div><div style="padding-left:40px;">    </div><div>Ancillary studies:</div><div>1. Special stain: Giemsa stain</div><div>2. Immunohistochemical stain: AE1/AE3.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
