    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Chronic active gastritis with Helicobacter pylori infection</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows gastric tissue with abundant infiltrate of mixed inflammatory cells in the lamina propria. Helicobacter pylori microorganisms are identified in the mucus layer as well as in the gastric pits and are <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">highlighted by H.P. immunostain. No evidence of malignancy is noted.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Immunohistochemical stain: H.P.</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Chronic atrophic gastritis with ECL cell hyperplasia</title>
    <created>20180925T065655Z</created>
    <updated>20250305T055227Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Chronic atrophic gastritis with ECL cell hyperplasia.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows gastric mucosal tissue with chronic inflammatory infiltrate in the lamina propria and increased distance between the individual glands, accompanied by intestinal metaplasia. There is proliferation of bland-looking cells</div><div>with finely dispersed chromatin, which are highlighted by synaptophysin and AE1/AE3, suggesting enterochromaffin-like</div><div>(ECL) cell hyperplasia.</div><div><br/></div><div>No Helicobacter Pylori is demonstrated by Giemsa stain.</div><hr/><div><a href="evernote:///view/26224745/s227/ea03d050-860e-494a-9305-ef3cd7c3de5c#a153d128-674d-4e02-bb65-bf26b5197321/7d628a7e-81db-4374-baf7-db2e8ef098ff/">Autoimmune gastritis</a></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20210714T091755Z</created>
    <updated>20241231T030001Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>chronic atrophic gastritis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows gastric mucosal tissue with chronic inflammatory infiltrate in the lamina propria and increased distance between the individual glands.</div><div>No Helicobater Pylori is demonstrated by Giemsa stain.</div><div>No invasive carcinoma is demonstrated by AE1/AE3.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Chronic colitis, no CMV [CI]</title>
