  <note>
    <title>Chronic ulcer (no HP)</title>
    <created>20171208T075756Z</created>
    <updated>20180129T055637Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Chronic ulcer</span><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Microsoft YaHei';">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Microsoft YaHei';">The gastric tissue reveals partial destruction of the mucosa with mild infiltrate of chronic inflammatory cells as well as a few neutrophils in the lamina propria. Necrotic debris are seen over the destructed surface. No Helicobacter pylori microorganisms are identified by H.P. immunostain. No malignancy is observed.</span></div><div><br style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>CMV, Cytomegalovirus infection</title>
