<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The colonic glands are thrown into serrations due to</div><div>goblet cell hyperplasia of the lining cells. There is focally crowded crypts stuctures with midly hyperchromatic nuclei. MLH1 shows intact nuclear staining excluding SSL with dysplasia.</div></en-note>      ]]>
