  <note>
    <title>Colon EMR</title>
    <created>20170112T052914Z</created>
    <updated>20251230T090139Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Adenocarcinoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>1. Tumor histological type: adenocarcinoma</div><div>2. Tumor size: cm</div><div>3. Histological grade: well / moderately /poorly differentiated; undifferentiated</div><div>4. Invasion depth: submucosa (T1)</div><div>5 Tumor Budding: Number of tumor buds in 1 “hotspot” field (specify total number in  area=0.785 mm2)</div><div>___ Low score (0-4) ___Intermediate score (5-9) ___High score (10 or more) ___  Cannot be determined</div><div>6. Type of polyp in which invasive carcinoma arose: __Tubular adenoma; __Tubulovillous  adenoma; __Villous</div><div>adenoma; __Hyperplastic polyp; __ Sessile serrated adenoma/polyp; __ Traditional  serrated adenoma;</div><div>7. Depth of submucosa invasion: &lt;1 mm/ >1mm</div><div>8. Angiolymphatic invasion: present / absent</div><div>9. Perineural invasion: present / absent</div><div>10. Margin: uninvolved/difficult to define in this specimen) (if close, ---- mm distance)</div><ol start="11"><li><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(255, 0, 0);">pTNM</span></span></span> <span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(1, 1, 1);">:   pT___N___( AJCC 8th Edition)</span></span></span></div></li><li><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(1, 1, 1);">Immunohistochemical stain:  (Results reported in previous specimen _)</span></span></span></div></li><ul><li><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(1, 1, 1);">    EGFR: _+ intensity of membranous staining in _% of</span></span></span></div></li><li><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(1, 1, 1);">    tumor cells.</span></span></span></div></li><li><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(1, 1, 1);">    IHC Testing for Mismatch Repair (MMR) Proteins</span></span></span></div></li><li><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(1, 1, 1);">    1. MLH1:intact nuclear expression</span></span></span></div></li><li><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(1, 1, 1);">    2. MSH2:intact nuclear expression</span></span></span></div></li><li><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(1, 1, 1);">    3. MSH6:intact nuclear expression</span></span></span></div></li><li><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(1, 1, 1);">    4. PMS2:intact nuclear expression</span></span></span></div></li></ul></ol><div style="padding-left:120px;"><span style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color:rgb(1, 1, 1);">IHC Interpretation: No loss of nuclear expression of MMR proteins: low probability of microsatellite instability-high (MSI-H)</span></span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Colon_MMR</title>
    <created>20170220T021342Z</created>
    <updated>20231124T013052Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><div align="left" style="min-height: 13pt;"><font color="#222222" face="arial"><span style="font-size:12pt">COMMENT: There are exceptions to the above IHC interpretations. These results should not be considered in isolation, and clinical correlation with genetic counseling is recommended to assess the need for germline testing.</span></font></div><div align="left" style="min-height: 13pt;"><font color="#222222" face="arial"><span style="font-size:12pt">NOTE I: (Interpretation of the test)</span></font></div><ul style="margin-top: 0mm; margin-bottom: 0mm; margin-left: 0mm; padding-left: 0pt;list-style-type: disc;"><li style="margin-left: 33pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size: 12pt;  color: #010101;"><font color="#222222" face="arial"><span style="font-size:12pt; font-family:arial; color:#222222; font-weight:Normal; font-style:Normal; font-decoration:Normal">No loss of nuclear expression of MMR proteins: low probability of microsatellite instability-high (MSI-H)</span></font></li><li style="margin-left: 33pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size: 12pt;  color: #010101;"><font color="#222222" face="arial"><span style="font-size:12pt; font-family:arial; color:#222222; font-weight:Normal; font-style:Normal; font-decoration:Normal">Loss of nuclear expression of MLH1 and PMS2: testing for methylation of the MLH1 promoter and/or mutation of BRAF is indicated (the presence of a BRAF V600E mutation and/or MLH1 methylation suggests that the tumor is sporadic and germline evaluation is probably not indicated; absence of both MLH1 methylation and of BRAF V600E mutation suggests the possibility of Lynch syndrome, and sequencing and/or large deletion/duplication testing of germline MLH1 may be indicated)</span></font></li><li style="margin-left: 33pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size: 12pt;  color: #010101;"><font color="#222222" face="arial"><span style="font-size:12pt; font-family:arial; color:#222222; font-weight:Normal; font-style:Normal; font-decoration:Normal">Loss of nuclear expression of MSH2 and MSH6: high probability of Lynch syndrome (sequencing and/or large deletion/duplication testing of germline MSH2 may be indicated, and, if negative, sequencing and/or large deletion/duplication testing of germline MSH6 may be indicated)</span></font></li><li style="margin-left: 33pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size: 12pt;  color: #010101;"><font color="#222222" face="arial"><span style="font-size:12pt; font-family:arial; color:#222222; font-weight:Normal; font-style:Normal; font-decoration:Normal">Loss of nuclear expression of MSH6 only: high probability of Lynch syndrome (sequencing and/or large deletion/duplication testing of germline MSH6 may be indicated)</span></font></li><li style="margin-left: 33pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; text-indent:0pt; font-size: 12pt;  color: #010101;"><font color="#222222" face="arial"><span style="font-size:12pt; font-family:arial; color:#222222; font-weight:Normal; font-style:Normal; font-decoration:Normal">Loss of nuclear expression of PMS2 only: high probability of Lynch syndrome (sequencing and/or large deletion/duplication testing of germline PMS2 may be indicated)</span></font></li></ul><div align="left" style="min-height: 11pt;"><div><font color="#999999" face="arial" size="2"><span style="font-size:10pt">Reference: CAP Template for Reporting Results of Biomarker Testing of Specimens From Patients With Carcinoma of the Colon and Rectum Version: 1.2.0.0</span></font></div><div><span style="font-family: arial;"><span style="color: rgb(153, 153, 153);"><br/></span></span></div></div><div align="left" style="min-height: 13pt;"><font color="#222222" face="arial"><span style="font-size:12pt">NOTE II:</span></font></div><div align="left" style="min-height: 13pt;"><font color="#222222" face="arial"><span style="font-size:12pt">Most pathologists regard convincingly strong expression of MMR proteins within</span></font> <font color="#FF0000" face="arial"><span style="font-size:12pt">>10%</span></font> <font color="#222222" face="arial"><span style="font-size:12pt">of the tumor as indicative of preserved (intact) expression.</span></font></div><div align="left" style="min-height: 11pt;"><div><font color="#999999" face="arial" size="2"><span style="font-size:10pt">Reference: Am J Surg Pathol 2016;40:e17¡Ve34.</span></font></div></div></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Colonic inertia</title>
    <created>20250422T031938Z</created>
    <updated>20260324T031423Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Colon, total abdominal colectomy --- Vascular congestion and fibrosis, clinically colonic inertia.</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Received is a total colectomy specimen including ileum (_ cm in length, _ cm in diameter), appendix (_ cm in length, _ cm in diameter), and colon (_ cm in length, _ cm in circumference). The mucosa of colon is focally flattening with variable thickness of bowel wall. No tumor is seen.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div>A1: bilateral margins</div><div>A2: appendix</div><div>A3: ileocecal valve</div><div>A4-A8 colon</div><div>A9: pericolonic fat    </div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The colonic tissue shows variable thickness of muscularis propria with fibrosis, accompanied by vascular congestion of bowel wall. Ganglion cells are present throughout the colonic segments that were sampled. The appendix demonstrates fibrous obliteration.</div><div>No evidence of inflammation or infection is seen.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Condyloma acuminatum with high-grade anal intraepithelial neoplasia (AIN2)</title>
    <created>20160901T013138Z</created>
    <updated>20260323T054104Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section shows proliferation of squamous mucosa in papillary fronds with dysplastic  change extending into upper 2/3 of the mucosa, characterized by nuclear hyperchromasia  and presence of mitotic figures in the superficial layer. Immunohistochemically, the  dysplastic cells show block-like p16 positivity. Ki-67 staining shows increased  proliferation index in these dysplastic cells. </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20200505T050348Z</created>
    <updated>20230608T053834Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>consistent with angiodysplasia.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows ectatic capillaries in the mucosa consistent</div><div>with angiodysplasia.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Consistent with gastritis cystica polyposa</title>
    <created>20180413T073504Z</created>
    <updated>20200207T090245Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Consistent with gastritis cystica polyposa</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows gastric mucosal tissue with dilated cystic glands in the mucosa within muscularis mucosae.</div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;">No Helicobacter Pylori is seen. </span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>consistent with hypertrophied anal papilla.</title>
    <created>20220208T053610Z</created>
    <updated>20220208T053617Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>consistent with hypertrophied anal papilla.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows loose fibrovascular tissue covered by squamous epithelium with focal papillary hyperplasia accompanied by infiltrate of acute and chronic inflammatory cells. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>consistent with hypertrophied papillae.</title>
