  <note>
    <title>Diverticulae</title>
    <created>20250219T070856Z</created>
    <updated>20250219T071105Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Diverticulae.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show mucosa and submucosa herniating through the muscularis propria, with thinning of muscle layers and  surrounding chronic inflammation.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Ectopic pancreas</title>
    <created>20170315T235343Z</created>
    <updated>20241216T055905Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Ectopic pancreas.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show lobules of ectopic pancreatic tissue in the submucosal and muscularis propria of the gastric tissue, revealing pancreatic acini, islet cells, and pancreatic  ducts.</div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12px;">No Helicobacter Pylori is seen. </span></span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>eosinophil-predominant inflammation</title>
    <created>20240630T062236Z</created>
    <updated>20240701T050902Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>eosinophil-predominant inflammation</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description</div><div>Section shows esophageal mucosal tissue with eosinophil-predominant inflammation and eosinophilc microabscess formation.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><hr/><div>eosinophil-predominant inflammation (r/o Eosinophilic esophagitis)</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description</div><div>Section shows basal cell hyperplasia accompanied by numerous eosinophils distributed along the entire epithelial thickness with degranulation. Eosinophilic microabscess are seen. Intercellular edema is prominent. Eosinophilic esophagitis should be considered. Please correlate.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Equivocal CMV</title>
    <created>20180925T060629Z</created>
    <updated>20250213T051037Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Equivocal CMV</div><div><br/></div><div>Anti-CMV immunostain shows focal</div><div>equivocal staining intensity in the stromal cells.</div><div>Please correlate clinically and do serology test for</div><div>antibodies to cytomegalovirus if clinically indicated.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><hr/><div>Equivocal CMV</div><div>The anti-CMV immunostain shows focal and equivocal staining intensity in the stromal cells. However, in the HE-stained section, there are no obvious CMV inclusion bodies. Please correlate clinically and do serology test for antibodies to cytomegalovirus if clinically indicated.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20190306T050212Z</created>
    <updated>20230525T073448Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Erosion.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows gastric mucosal tissue with superficial erosion accompanied by chronic inflammatory infiltrate in the lamina propria. </div><div>No Helicobater Pylori is seen. </div><div>No malignancy is observed.        </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Esophagus HP</title>
