  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Fistula + EH</title>
    <created>20170420T065103Z</created>
    <updated>20240229T063933Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>1. Fistula , anus, fistulotomy</div><div>2. External hemorrhoid, anus, hemorrhoidectomy</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>1. The section reveals a squamous-lined tissue in which a granulation-line fistulous</div><div>   tract is noted, extending from the squamous surface into the inner and deeper</div><div>   connective tissue stroma. There is accompanying round cell as well as</div><div>   polymorphonuclear cell infiltration around the tract and its adjacent tissue.</div><div><br/></div><div>2. The section reveals anal tissue in which the underlying stroma are occupied by</div><div>   variably dilated or congested vessels filled with RBCs.</div><div>    </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Fistula + external hemorrhoid + abscess</title>
    <created>20170420T065103Z</created>
    <updated>20211223T094653Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>1. Fistula with abscess formation.</div><div>2. External hemorrhoid.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The section reveals a squamous-lined tissue in which a granulation-lined fistulous tract is noted, extending from the squamous surface into the inner and deeper connective tissue stroma. There is accompanying round cell as well as</div><div>polymorphonuclear cell infiltration around the tract and its adjacent tissue. Focal abscess formation is seen.</div><div>Variably dilated or congested vessels filled with RBCs are seen consistent with hemorroid.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Fistula with abscess formation.</title>
