      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>mild chronic inflammation.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows gastric mucosal tissue with mild chronic inflammatory infiltrate in the lamina propria.  </div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;">No Helicobacter Pylori is seen. </span></div><div>No malignancy is observed.<span>    </span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Mixed Adenoma-Serrated Polyp (MASP) [TSA+SSA]</title>
    <created>20181229T050006Z</created>
    <updated>20230821T030829Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>mixed adenoma-serrated polyp.  </div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a focus of traditional serrated adenoma with cytologic dysplasia arising next to a sessile serrated lesion with dilated crypt bases.</div><div><br/></div><div>NOTE: most common TSA and SSA/P.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Mixed adenoma-serrated polyp MASP</title>
    <created>20190403T071342Z</created>
    <updated>20250130T150247Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>mixed adenoma-serrated polyp.  </div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows polypoid tissue composed of adenoma (low-grade dysplasia) and hyperplastic polyp ( with a relatively sharp transition between them. )</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20210218T075205Z</created>
    <updated>20251225T074346Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Mucormycosis (Zygomycosis).</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows necrotic debris and inflammatory cells admixed</div><div>with several broad hyphae which is thin-walled, pauciseptate</div><div>and with wide-angle branching, consistent with Mucormycosis</div><div>(Zygomycosis).</div><div><br/></div><hr/><div>Fungal hyphae identified (see comment).</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic Description:</div><div>The section shows lung tissue with abundant fungal elements, including several broad hyphae which are thin-walled and pauciseptate.</div><div><br/></div><div>Comment:</div><div>Fungal infection such as mucormycosis should be considered. The differential diagnosis includes aspergillosis. Correlation with microbial cultures (or molecular analysis) is essential if determination of fungal species is required for clinical management.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20180820T024500Z</created>
    <updated>20181123T050225Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Mucosal schwann cell hamartoma</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows polypoid colonic mucosal tissue with uniform, bland-looking spindle cells in the lamina propria. These spindle cells shows elongated, wavy nuclei, fine chromatin, and indistinct nucleoli, abundant eosinophilic cytoplasm and ill-defined cell borders. Entrapped crypts are seen.</div><div><br/></div><div>By immunohistochemistry, these spindles cells are positive for S-100, but negative for desmin, SMA, CD117 or EMA.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Mucosal tag [COLtag]</title>
    <created>20161214T054157Z</created>
    <updated>20230526T062451Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">mucosal tag.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>Section shows benign colonic mucosal tissue without significant inflammation <span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">or dysplastic change. </span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: gotham;"><br/></span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Mucosal tag [STOtag]</title>
    <created>20161214T054157Z</created>
    <updated>20241210T024454Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">mucosal tag.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">The section shows a tiny fragment of benign gastric mucosal tissue without significant inflammation or dysplastic changes.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">No Helicobacter pylori is seen. No malignancy is observed.</span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>NET neuroendocrine tumor</title>
    <created>20170726T233525Z</created>
    <updated>20260513T022743Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>G1, well-differentiated neuroendocrine tumor </div><div>G2, well-differentiated neuroendocrine tumor</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Histologic type: Neuroendocrine tumor</div><div>Histological grade: G1/G2/G3</div><div>G1: mitotic count, &lt; 2 per 2mm2 and/or &lt;3% Ki67 index</div><div>G2: mitotic count, 2-20 per 2mm2 and/or 3-20% Ki67 index</div><div>G3: mitotic count, >20 per 2mm2 and/or >20% Ki67 index</div><div>Tumor size: _ mm in greatest dimension</div><div>Tumor focality: Unifocal/Multifocal (specify number of tumors: ______)</div><div>Mitotic Rate:  ___ /10 HPF</div><div>Microscopic Tumor Extension: </div><div>_ Tumor invades lamina propria</div><div>_ Tumor invades into but not through muscularis mucosae</div><div>_ Tumor invades submucosa</div><div>_ Tumor invades muscularis propria</div><div>_ Tumor invades through the muscularis propria into the subserosal adipose tissue or the nonperitonealized pericolic or perirectal soft tissues but does not extend to the serosal surface (visceral peritoneum) </div><div>_ Tumor penetrates serosa (visceral peritoneum) </div><div>_ Tumor directly invades adjacent structures (specify: </div><div>_ Tumor penetrates to the surface of the visceral peritoneum (serosa) and directly invades adjacent structures (specify: </div><div>Lymphovascular invasion: Not identified</div><div>Perineural invasion: Not identified</div><div>Margins: Free/ &lt;1 mm / involved; Distance of tumor from closest margin: ___ mm or ___ cm</div><div>Additional Pathologic Findings:</div><div>_ Tumor necrosis</div><div>Immunohistochemical stains:</div><div>- INSM1: </div><div>- Synaptophysin: </div><div>-  Chromogranin A: </div><div>-   Ki-67 labeling index: &lt;3%  3%-20%  >20%</div><div>- AE1/AE3: </div><div>pTNM: </div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been reviewed by two pathologists.)</div><div><br/></div><div>Primary Tumor (pT)# ___ pTX: Primary tumor cannot be assessed ___ pT0: No evidence of primary tumor ___ pT1: Tumor invades the lamina propria or submucosa and is ≤2 cm ___ pT1a: Tumor &lt;1 cm in greatest dimension ___ pT1b: Tumor 1-2 cm in greatest dimension ___ pT2: Tumor invades the muscularis propria or is >2 cm with invasion of the lamina propria or submucosa ___ pT3: Tumor invades through the muscularis propria into subserosal tissue without penetration of overlying serosa ___ pT4: Tumor invades visceral peritoneum (serosa) or other organs or other adjacent structures</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>no SM [nosm]</title>
    <created>20200902T015756Z</created>
    <updated>20260417T083156Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Mild chronic inflammation. see note.</div><div><br/></div><div>NOTE: No submucosal tissue is present in this specimen for evaluation. Re-biopsy is suggested if clinically indicated.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows gastric mucosal tissue with mild chronic</div><div>inflammatory infiltrate in the lamina propria.</div><div>No Helicobacter Pylori is seen.</div><div>No malignancy is observed. However, no submucosal tissue is present in this specimen for evaluation. Re-biopsy is suggested if clinically indicated.    </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Not representative, re-biopsy</title>
