<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Note: The specimen may be not representative for the lesion. Re-biopsy is recommended.</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>PDCA_stomach stoadeno</title>
    <created>20160726T071219Z</created>
    <updated>20230404T085100Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Poorly differentiated adenocarcinoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows gastric tissue infiltrated by poorly differentiated neoplastic cells in cords and small nests with focal glandular differentiation. Signet-ring cells are also seen. Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are highlighted by cytokeratin (AE1/AE3).</div><div>The findings are consistent with a poorly differentiated adenocarcinoma.</div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;">No Helicobacter Pylori is seen.</span></div><div><br/></div><div>Her-2 (by immunohistochemistry): </div><div>+___ Negative (score 0) + ___ Negative (score 1+) + ___ Equivocal (score 2+) + ___ Positive (score 3+) + ___ Cannot be determined</div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been reviewed by two pathologists.)</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><en-media hash="d2765bbe5be4e4150ad35c0f078d7621" type="image/png" /></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
    <resource>
      <data encoding="base64">
