  <note>
    <title>Perforated gastric ulcer; stomach (PPU)</title>
    <created>20170221T092750Z</created>
    <updated>20231214T074046Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Perforated gastric ulcer.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a deep ulcerative process that penetrates into the muscular and serosal layers, with concomitant collagenous scarring of the adjacent muscular wall.</div><div>Fungal spores are seen admixed with necrotic debris, and are highlighted by GMS and PAS stainings. No viral inclusion is highlighted by anti-CMV immunostain. No evidence</div><div>of malignancy is noted.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20200930T073951Z</created>
    <updated>20250402T065236Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>perineurioma (benign fibroblastic polyp).</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows spindle cells proliferation with separation of colonic crypts. These spindle cells are bland-looking with pale indistinct cytoplasm. Immunohistochemically, the lesional cells are focally positive for EMA but not CD34,DOG-1, desmin, or S100, consistent with the diagnosis.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>phlebosclerotic colitis_biopsy</title>
    <created>20191220T061701Z</created>
    <updated>20230920T060211Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Ischemic change, consistent with phlebosclerotic colitis (see description).</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows deposition of collagen in the lamina propria and around blood vessels in the mucosa consistent</div><div>with ischemic change. Focal infiltrate of mixed inflammatory cells is algo seen. Congo red is negative for amyloid deposition.</div><div><br/></div><div>The characteristic features of phlebosclerotic colitis, which include calcification and thrombosis of the mesenteric</div><div>veins, are difficult to be evaluated in the mucosal biopsy.</div><div><br/></div><div>Together with the imaging findings, it can be consistent but not pathognomonic for phlebosclerotic colitis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Correlate with clinical history of taking Chinese herbs is mandatory.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20210805T071318Z</created>
    <updated>20231225T071109Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Poorly differentiated adenocarcinoma with signet ring cells.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows gastric tissue with poorly differentiated neoplastic signet-ring cells infiltrating the lamina propria. Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are highlighted by cytokeratin (AE1/AE3) but not GATA3.</div><div>No Helicobacter Pylori is seen.</div><div><br/></div><div>Her-2 (by immunohistochemistry): </div><div>+___ Negative (score 0) + ___ Negative (score 1+) + ___ Equivocal (score 2+) + ___ Positive (score 3+) + ___ Cannot be determined</div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been peer reviewed by two doctors.)</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>PPI effect</title>
    <created>20180417T045837Z</created>
    <updated>20180417T045844Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Some parietal cells show cytoplasmic swelling and vacuolation, which is probably due to PPI effects.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>PPU+vagotomy (duodenum)</title>
    <created>20170103T010345Z</created>
    <updated>20250220T050419Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <reminder-order>1687157776274</reminder-order>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>Ulceration, cosistent with perforated peptic ulcer.</div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The duodenal tissue shows a deep, benign ulcerative process that penetrates into the muscular and serosal layers, with concomitant collagenous scarring of the adjacent muscular wall. The latter displays mixed inflammatory cell infiltration with predominance of mononuclear cells. The  outer serosal surface exhibits acute inflammatory reaction.</div><div><br/></div><div>Confirmed, nerve bungles.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows presence of histologically unremarkable nerve bundles enveloped by its perineural sheath.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Presence of gastric type mucosa (esophagus)</title>
    <created>20161213T004257Z</created>
    <updated>20230721T032607Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>chronic inflammation with presence of gastric-type mucosa.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows esophageal tissue with presence of gastric glands of cardiac- fundic type, and chronic inflammatory infiltrate in the lamina propria. No intestinal metaplasia is noted.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Prolapsing mucosal polyp / Solitary rectal ulcer syndrome</title>
    <created>20211224T014849Z</created>
    <updated>20241106T081328Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Prolapsing mucosal polyp.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a polypoid lesion with superficial mucosal erosion, crypt hyperplasia and fibromuscular obliteration of the lamina propria.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><a href="https://www.pathologyoutlines.com/topic/colonmucosalprolapsepolyp.html">pathology outline</a></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>pseudolipomatosis</title>
    <created>20211027T090601Z</created>
    <updated>20230606T085743Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>pseudolipomatosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows colonic mucosal tissue with empty spaces within lamina propria, being negative for S100, consistent with the diagnosis.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Pseudomembranous colitis</title>
    <created>20170220T085306Z</created>
    <updated>20230518T091736Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>consistent with pseudomembranous colitis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>It shows colonic mucosal tissue with ballooned and dilated galnds with intercrypt necrosis, accompanied by mucopurulent exudate.</div><div><br/></div><div>--</div><div>consistent with pseudomembranous colitis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows mucopurulent exudate erupts out of crypts to form a mushroom-like cloud.</div><div>No viral inclusion is highlighted by anti-CMV immunostain.</div><div>No malignancy is observed.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>R/O Barrett&apos;s esophagus (no IM)</title>
    <created>20180116T034443Z</created>
    <updated>20241107T055810Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-url>
        https://www.google.com/search?rlz=1C1BEMX_zh-TWTW773TW773&amp;ei=Ky7WXYnbLq2Tr7wPyPuSwAw&amp;q=EG+junction&amp;oq=EG+junction&amp;gs_l=psy-ab.3..0l4j0i30l6.988872.991099..991308...1.0..0.89.608.12......0....1..gws-wiz.......0i67j0i131j0i10j0i8i30j0i8i10i30.G7nXKkOBrKc&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjJnI2Q1vrlAhWtyYsBHci9BMgQ4dUDCAs&amp;uact=5
      </source-url>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>R/O Barrett's esophagus    </div><div><br/></div><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div><span style="font-family: arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color:rgb(32, 33, 36);">Esophagogastric junction</span></span></span>, endoscopic biopsy --- <span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">Chronic inflammation.</span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">Microscopic description:</span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">Section shows juxtaposed squamous and gastric mucosal tissue with chronic inflammatory cells infiltrate within the lamina propria. Neither intestinal metaplasia nor malignancy is seen.    </span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">No fungus is highlighted by PAS.</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">No Helicobacter Pylori is demonstrated by H.P. immunostain. </span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px;">    </span></div><div>                        </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>r/o eosinophilic duodenitis</title>
    <created>20190325T082745Z</created>
    <updated>20230606T045057Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><div>duodenitis with eosinophilic inflammation (please see description).</div><div><br/></div><div>CLINICAL INFORMATION:</div><div>Lab data(____): WBC ___ x1000/uL; Neu %; Lym %; Mono %; Eos %; Baso %.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows duodenal mucosal tissue with infiltrate of</div><div>eosinophils within the lamina propria as well as in the</div><div>muscularis mucosae. Focal dense eosinophilic</div><div>infiltrate (>20 eosinophils/HPF) is noted. There are some</div><div>lymphoplasmacytic cells noted, too. Immunohistochemically,</div><div>no viral inclusion is demonstrated by anti-CMV immunostain.    </div><div>No fungus is highlighted by PAS.</div><div><br/></div><div>These findings are consistent but not pathognomonic for</div><div>eosinophilic duodenitis. Please correlate clinically.</div><hr/><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">The overall features are nonspecific finding that requires</span></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">clinical correlation.</span></div></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><a href="https://www.pathologyoutlines.com/topic/coloneosinophilic.html">https://www.pathologyoutlines.com/topic/coloneosinophilic.html</a></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Reactive foveolar hyperplasia</title>
    <created>20221027T134422Z</created>
    <updated>20250304T050413Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Reactive foveolar hyperplasia.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Secion shows proliferation of foveolar epithelium rather than deep pyloric glands</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>repeated bouts of inflammation and repair.</title>
    <created>20220701T061225Z</created>
    <updated>20220701T061300Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>The overall features indicates repeated bouts of inflammation and repair.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Resins</title>
    <created>20161231T031536Z</created>
    <updated>20240319T051255Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: Gotham; font-size: 12px;">Sevelamer/___ resins identified, See note</span></div><div><font face="Gotham" style="font-size: 12px;"><br/></font></div><div><span style="font-family: Gotham; font-size: 12px;">Note: In the small series available, Sevelamer was sometimes associated with mucosal injury.</span></div><div><font face="Gotham" style="font-size: 12px;"><br/></font></div><div><hr/><div><span style="font-family: Gotham; font-size: 12px;">Eosinophilic crystals identified, See note</span></div></div><div><font face="Gotham" style="font-size: 12px;"><br/></font></div><div><span style="font-family: Gotham; font-size: 12px;">Note: No clinical notes are available at time of slide review. Eosinophilic crystals are seen on H&amp;E. These structures are yellow on AFB and are suggestive of Bile Acid Sequestrants (BAS: Colesevelam (Welchol), Colestipol (Colestid), Cholestyramine (LoCholest, Prevalite, Questran). In the small series available, BAS have no established role in causing mucosal damage.</span></div><div><hr/><div><span>    </span><br/></div></div><div><font face="Gotham" style="font-size: 12px;"><br/></font></div><div><span style="font-family: Gotham; font-size: 12px;">Reference: Swanson BJ, Limketkai BN, Liu TC, Montgomery E, Nazari K, Park JY, Santangelo WC, Torbenson MS, Voltaggio L, Yearsley MM, Arnold CA. Sevelamer crystals in the gastrointestinal tract (GIT): a new entity associated with mucosal injury. Am J Surg Pathol. 2013 Nov;37(11):1686-93. ￼</span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Retention polyp</title>
    <created>20170117T005907Z</created>
    <updated>20201208T060556Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>retention polyp.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show a retention polyp with variably and cystically dilated glands with ulceration and granulation tissue at the surface. These glands are partially filled with mucinous material and are separated by inflamed and edematous stroma.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Sac</title>
    <created>20161213T004956Z</created>
    <updated>20250731T061619Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>__inguinal area, hernioplasty ---</div><div>Consistent with hernial sac.</div><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><div>The specimen consists of a piece of tissue measuring _</div><div>cm.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and submitted in one</div><div>cassette.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a saccular lesion composed of loose fibrous</div><div>connective tissue focally lined by mesothelial cells</div><div>revealing mild proliferation.</div><div><br/></div><div>    </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
