<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Ventral site, herniorraphy ---</div><div>consistent with hernial sac.</div><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><div>The specimen consists of a piece of tissue measuring _</div><div>cm.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and submitted in one</div><div>cassette.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a saccular lesion composed of loose fibrous</div><div>connective tissue focally lined by mesothelial cells</div><div>revealing mild proliferation.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
