      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Some parietal cells show cytoplasmic swelling and vacuolation, which is probably due to PPI effects.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Squamous papilloma, esophagus</title>
    <created>20161102T054458Z</created>
    <updated>20230626T070600Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>squamous papilloma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows an exophytic lesion comprising an arborescence of vascular connective tissue clothed by a multilayered squamous epithelium. The latter is well differentiated and shows an orderly sequence of maturation. There is no evidence of malignancy.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>squamous papilloma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div style="padding-left:40px;">Section shows an exophytic lesion comprising fibrovascular  cores lined by squamous epithelium, which is well differentiated with an orderly sequence of maturation. There is no evidence of malignancy.</div><div>    </div><div><br/></div><div>                </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
