    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Sessile serrated lesion.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a sessile serrated lesion with dilated and L-shaped crypt bases.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>stoHP (PJ)</title>
    <created>20240703T062949Z</created>
    <updated>20240703T063014Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>hyperplastic polyp. see NOTE</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows elongation, turtousity and dilatation of the</div><div>gastric foveola, associated with focal stromal edema and</div><div>mild chronic inflammatory infiltration.</div><div>Immunohistochemically, no invasive carcinoma is demonstrated</div><div>by AE1/AE3. P53 shows no significant increase.</div><div>No Helicobacter Pylori is seen.</div><div><br/></div><div>NOTE: Aborizing cords of smooth muscle highlighted by desmin</div><div>suggest the possibility of Peutz-Jeghers polyp. In the</div><div>absence of clinical indications of P-J syndrome, this is</div><div>likely a hyperplastic polyp.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>STOHP 長得像PJ polyp</title>
    <created>20240626T022318Z</created>
    <updated>20240929T150207Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>hyperplastic polyp. see NOTE</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows elongation, turtousity and dilatation of the</div><div>gastric foveola, associated with focal stromal edema and</div><div>mild chronic inflammatory infiltration.</div><div>Immunohistochemically, no invasive carcinoma is demonstrated</div><div>by AE1/AE3. P53 shows no significant increase.</div><div>No Helicobacter Pylori is seen.</div><div><br/></div><div>NOTE: Aborizing cords of smooth muscle highlighted by desmin suggest the possibility of Peutz-Jeghers polyp. In the absence of clinical indications of P-J syndrome, this is likely a hyperplastic polyp.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20210511T063933Z</created>
    <updated>20210511T063946Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>suggestive of lipoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows expanded adipose tissue in the submucosa and</div><div>lamina propria, suggestive of lipoma.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Synaptophysin to exclude neuroendocrine lesion [r/o NE]</title>
    <created>20210115T023632Z</created>
    <updated>20240328T080701Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Some strands of epithelioid cells are seen in the lamina propria, propbably representing tangential cut of crypts. These cells are negative for synaptophygin, and excluding neuroendocrine lesion.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>TA</title>
    <created>20161222T065009Z</created>
    <updated>20231017T082223Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">tubular adenoma.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>Section shows crowded tubuloglandular structures that are lined by tall columnar epithelium in which individual cells exhibit mild dysplasia. No frank malignancy is noted.</div><div><span>    </span><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>TA + cauterized artifact</title>
