      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Tubular adenoma at least</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows crowded tubuloglandular structures that are lined by tall columnar epithelium in which individual cells exhibit mild dysplasia. Underlying high-grade dysplasia or invasiveness cannot be excluded.</div><div>    </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>TA HG (architectual + cytology)</title>
    <created>20171206T054204Z</created>
    <updated>20230901T075935Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: arial;"><span style="font-size: 9pt;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">Tubular adenoma with focal high-grade dysplasia.</span></span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: arial;"><span style="font-size: 9pt;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">Microscopic description:</span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: arial;"><span style="font-size: 9pt;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">Section shows crowded tubuloglandular structures that are lined by tall columnar epithelium in which individual cells exhibit mild dysplasia.</span></span></span> <span style="font-family: arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 13px;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">Focal high-grade dysplasia which shows rounded, heaped-up cells with open chromatin and prominent nucleoli, as well as architectural complexity are noted. </span></span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 13px;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">The surgical margin is free of adenoma.</span></span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: arial;"><span style="font-size: 9pt;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">The surgical margin cannot be adequately assessed due to piecemeal removal.</span></span></span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>TA with squamoid morules</title>
    <created>20251029T020254Z</created>
    <updated>20251029T020414Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="display:none;--en-chs:&quot;&quot;"> </div><div>Tubular adenoma with squamoid morules.</div><div><br/></div><div>Ancillary studies:</div><div>Focal solid nests of squamoid cells are seen, which are positive for CK5/6 but not p40, consistent with squamoid morules.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>TA+COL8</title>
    <created>20180507T090348Z</created>
    <updated>20231017T084702Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>-- tubular adenoma.</div><div>-- hyperplastic polyp.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:    </div><div>Section shows polypoid tissue comosed of crowded tubuloglandular structures lined by dysplastic epithelial cells, as well as tissue composed of colonic glands thrown into serrations due to goblet cell hyperplasia of the lining cells.                             </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>TA+SSA (SSL)</title>
    <created>20180503T015910Z</created>
    <updated>20191104T022114Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Tubular adenoma and sessile serrated lesion</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows polypoid tissue comosed of crowded tubuloglandular structures lined by dysplastic epithelial cells, as well as proliferative glands with serration, and <span>    </span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>TSA</title>
    <created>20160715T025801Z</created>
    <updated>20230821T030827Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">traditional serrated adenoma.</span></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a polyp featuring hyperplastic, crowded glands lined by columnar cells with eosinophilic cytoplasm and pencillate nuclei. They are characterized by serrated architectural and villiform growth patterns surrounded by inflamed lamina propria. Ectopic crypt formations are seen.</div><div>No frank malignancy is identified.    </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Tubulovillous adenoma</title>
    <created>20170306T061311Z</created>
    <updated>20250424T070937Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-url>https://app.expertpath.com/document/adenoma-colon/52b29689-3baf-4e63-ace1-a72bfd9aba92</source-url>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="text-align:start;color:rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="font-family: arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 13px;">DIAGNOSIS: </span></span><span style="font-family: arial;"><span style="font-size: 9pt;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">Tubulovillous adenoma </span></span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div style="text-align:start;color:rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="font-family: arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 13px;">Section shows a polyp with presence of both villous and tubular components in which the epithelial linings featuring nuclear hyperchromatism and pseudostratification.</span></span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20220401T081737Z</created>
    <updated>20241204T092812Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Tubulovillous adenoma at least.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows both villous and tubuloglandular structures lined by dysplastic epithelium. Underlying high-grade dysplasia or invasiveness cannot be excluded.</div><div>    </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>TVA HG dysplasia (architectual + cytology)</title>
    <created>20161028T051638Z</created>
    <updated>20231006T084645Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: arial;">tubulovillous adenoma with focal high-grade dysplasia.</span></div><div><br/></div><div style="text-align:start;"><span style="font-family: arial;"><span style="font-size: 9pt;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">Microscopic description:</span></span></span></div><div style="text-align:start;color:rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="font-family: arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 13px;">The original and deeper-cut sections show a polyp with presence of both villous and tubular components in which the epithelial linings featuring pseudostratification and hyperchromatism. Focal high-grade dysplasia which shows rounded, heaped-up cells with open chromatin and prominent nucleoli, as well as architectural complexity is noted. </span></span></div><div><br/></div><div style="text-align:start;color:rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="font-family: arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 13px;">The surgical margin is free of adenoma.</span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: arial;"><span style="font-size: 9pt;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">The surgical margin cannot be adequately assessed due to piecemeal removal.</span></span></span></div><div>    </div><div>(This case has been peer reviewed by two doctors.)</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>UC vs infectious colitis</title>
    <created>20181231T072402Z</created>
    <updated>20241227T052347Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>chronic active colitis with cryptitis and crypt abscesses (please see description).</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows mild and focal crypt architectural distortion, lymphoplasmacytic expansion of the lamina propria, cryptitis and crypt abscesses. Many neutrophils are also seen within the lamina propria.</div><div>NOTE: The overall findings are not pathognomonic but consistent with ulcerative colitis. However, presence of many neutrophils within the lamina propria is more favor of infectious colitis. The initial episode of ulcerative colitis may histologically appear similar to infectious colitis; therefore, infectious etiologies should be excluded prior to confirming a diagnosis of ulcerative colitis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, no viral inclusions are demonstrated by anti-CMV immunostain.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Ulcer + Fungus / No HP</title>
    <created>20220309T082808Z</created>
    <updated>20251015T052920Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Ulceration with fungal infection.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The gastric tissue fragments reveal partial destruction of the mucosa with marked infiltration by mixed inflammatory cells in the lamina propria. Necrotic debris are seen over the destructed surface as well as separate fragments. No Helicobacter pylori microorganisms are highlighted by Giemsa stain. Fungal spores and hyphae are seen.</div><div><br/></div><div>Ancillary studies:</div><div>Special stain: Giemsa stain.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Ulcer [esoUlcer]</title>
    <created>20211126T044358Z</created>
    <updated>20250508T054550Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>ulceration.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows squamous mucosal tissue with ulceration, and mixed inflammatory infiltrate.</div><div>No fungus is highlighted by PAS. No invasive carcinoma is demonstrated by AE1/AE3.   </div><div><span style="font-size: 12px;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">No viral inclusion is demonstrated by anti-CMV or HSV immunostain.        </span></span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Ulcer with Helicobacter pylori infection, stomach (with W-S stain)</title>
    <created>20160830T072725Z</created>
    <updated>20230704T093128Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section shows gastric tissue revealing focal ulceration with mixed inflammatory infiltrate in the lamina propria. Helicobacter pylori microorganisms are demonstrated by Warthin-Starry stain. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Ulcer with HP and fungal infection, stomach [ulcer+hp+fungus]</title>
    <created>20170103T005228Z</created>
    <updated>20260428T055022Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>ulceration with Helicobacter pylori and fungal infection.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The gastric tissue fragments reveal partial destruction of the mucosa with marked infiltration by mixed inflammatory cells in the lamina propria. Necrotic debris are seen over the destructed surface as well as separate fragments. Helicobacter pylori</div><div>microorganisms are identified in the surface of the adjacent mucosa and in the gastric pits, which are highlighted by Giemsa stain. Fungal spores and hyphae are seen, which are also highlighted by PAS. No invasive carcinoma is demonstrated by AE1/AE3. </div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">Ancillary studies:</span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">1. Special stain:</span></span> <span style="font-size: 9pt;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">Giemsa stain, PAS.</span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt;"><span style="color:rgb(34, 34, 34);">2. Immunohistochemical stain: AE1/AE3.</span></span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Ulcer with HP infection [Ulcer HP]</title>
