  </note>
  <note>
    <title>申覆 GI</title>
    <created>20220210T085118Z</created>
    <updated>20251209T075919Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>This case is a clinically gastric ulcer, r/o malignancy.</div><div><br/></div><div>There is dense infiltrate of inflammatory cells within the lamina propria, in which a poorly-differentiated adenocarcinoma could be overlooked solely on HE-stained section. AE1/AE3 is perfromed to exclude malignancy.  Thank you.</div><div><br/></div><div>There is a dense lymphoid infiltrate with nodular pattern that the differential diagnosis include lymphoid hyperplasia and follicular lymphoma.</div><div>CD3, CD20, and bcl2 are performed to exclude follicular lymphoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Crohn disease is suspected by clinician.</div><div>CMV can complicate with IBD, asides with equivical stroma. cells, anti-CMV immunostain is performed to exclude CMV infection.</div><div>CD68 is performed to see if there is granuloma which is usually poorly formed  in Crohn disease and could be difficultly seen on HE stain0</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
</en-export>
